description:
&lt;p&gt;The NIHR Leicester Biomedical Research Centre-Cardiovascular Theme, based at Glenfield Hospital, is looking to appoint a Research Governance Administrator to work in their state of the art facility providing advice and support to Investigators, ensuring that they have full access to the range of the high quality research management functions.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Research Governance Administrator will work as part of a team of staff, led by the Biomedical Research Centre Cardiovascular Theme Manager providing a key link between researchers, the Trust, University and external collaborators.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for an enthusiastic, motivated and dedicated individual with an understanding of research governance who is committed to ensuring that research is conducted on a highly professional and performance-driven basis. You will need to have good communication, interpersonal and organisational skills. The post holder will need to apply good practical understanding and knowledge of the UK-GCP research framework. The post-holder will be responsible for implementing national, best practice research management processes within the Trust, as directed by the BRC CV Governance Officer. They will be responsible for ensuring that the local integration of systems and processes is achieved so that individuals can benefit fully from streamlined systems and processes.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post provides an excellent opportunity for highly motivated individual to contribute to the performance and development of an internationally recognised centre of excellence in cardiovascular research.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Informal enquiries about the post are welcome and can be directed to Tara Maitland, Governance Officer; email tara.maitland@uhl-tr.nhs.uk telephone 0116 204 4737.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Tara Maitland - Research Governance Officer&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;tara.maitland@uhl-tr.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;0116 204 4737&lt;/p&gt;
